  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Oliver Johnson has decided to stay another day in Brooklyn. Since he fears that the compositors do not have enough copy to keep them busy, he requests that Maria Weston Chapman send them her sketch of the speeches made at Marlboro Chapel, except the remarks made by William Lloyd Garrison, who wants to revise them. Garrison gave a beautiful address here today about the &quot;pseudo World&apos;s Convention.&quot;</subfield>
